cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image colorization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method that involves training a variational autoencoder (VAE) to learn a low dimensional embedding of color fields, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The paper also discusses loss terms for the VAE decoder, which is a form of optimization (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions spatial co-ordination, which is a topic in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper deals with generating diverse colorizations, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
